column7: Determines whether the equipment uses S6F11 or S6F13 for event reporting.(1=S6F13  0=S6F11.
Determines the frequency of the heartbeat message (S1F1 in seconds.  0=never.
Determines whether S1F1 or S1F13 will be used for establishing communications.  1=S1F13; 0=S1F1.
Contains the time  in seconds to wait when attempting to establish communications with the host.
Whether to establish the TCP/IP socket session when opening the hsms session.  ACTIVE (communicate with existing session or PASSIVE (create new session.
If HSMSConnectMode is PASSIVE the port on which the TCP/IP socket session will be established.  If HSMSConnectMode is ACTIVE  the host and port to connect to in the format hostname:portnumber.
Whether to turn on spooling when there is no host communication.  1=turn on spooling; 0=no spooling.
ID of each virtual configuration.  Like sampling  report every nth part.
